			<h3 ><a href="#p17479" rel="nofollow"><!-- google_ad_section_start -->Re: Kendry Morales anyone?<!-- google_ad_section_end --></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><!-- google_ad_section_start(weight=ignore) --><a rel="nofollow" href="./viewtopic.php?p=17479&amp;sid=b251e3212c43240521883cbf129561f4#p17479"><img src="./styles/static/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>Post <a href="./viewtopic.php?p=17479&amp;sid=b251e3212c43240521883cbf129561f4#p17479" onclick="prompt('Direct link to post:',this.href); return false;"><strong>#47</strong></a>&nbsp;by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=147&amp;sid=b251e3212c43240521883cbf129561f4" style="color: #000000;" class="username-coloured">A_K</a></strong> &raquo; December 19th, 2012, 8:38 pm <!-- google_ad_section_end --></p>

			

			<div id="explanation17479" style="display:none" >
					<form action="" method="post">
						<fieldset>
							<textarea name="comment_text" cols="60" rows="5"></textarea><br />
							<input name="comment_to_id" type="hidden" value="147" />
							<input name="Submit" type="submit" class="button1" value="Submit" />
						</fieldset>
					</form>
			</div>



			<div class="content"><!-- google_ad_section_start --><blockquote><div><cite>ofahn wrote:</cite><br />I posted this previously in the string about Morales.<br /><br /><br /><br />I'm wondering how much of this went into LA's thinking.</div></blockquote><br /><br />I can imagine that they'd have a tough time finding a market for Wells, who is basically a replacement-level player but who gets paid $21 million per year. That's... not particularly appealing. <br /><br />But damn, why not just accept it as a sunk cost and put him on the bench while you let the better player take the at bats? <br /><br />Wanting to add MLB-ready bullpen pieces is all well and good, but there are easier ways to do it. The nature of relievers is that you should never trade good, young sluggers for them (even if your good young slugger is a Boras client approaching free agency).<br /><br />I should point out that I mention Saunders only as an example. There are plenty of Vargas-level pitchers out there if that's what you want, but it's hard to justify giving up a Morales-level hitter to get one, regardless of the circumstances.<!-- google_ad_section_end --></div>
						

