			<div class="content"><!-- google_ad_section_start -->I hate to sound like a broken record, but I have to say once again: if what you desire is a league-average fly ball pitcher who will be made better by a spacious home park and a fantastic defensive outfield, there are better ways to acquire one than by giving up a good, young hitter who would unquestionably be your team's best DH option. <br /><br />It's not that Vargas is useless. If you're in &quot;win now&quot; mode, you should keep Morales and go get a Vargas-level player without giving up anything.<!-- google_ad_section_end --></div>
						

